This paper is primarily focused on deep learning-based face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses algorithmic discrimination, which is related to fairness and ethics in machine learning, and could potentially fall under the categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning models and experimentation with different demographic groups could also be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM).
